        <h2 class="py-4 italic font-semibold">We build the basics, you build the rest.</h2>

        <p class="py-4">We approached Landscape’s functionality and design with the utmost simplicity. We believe people should be able to shape the environment they use to stay connected. Not Tlon or any other company. We simply set the scene with a few core primitives to get you started.</p>
        <p class="py-4">Built on Urbit, it provides the freedom to mold these utilities on an individual basis, ensuring the platform will complement our personal needs and withstand change well into the future.</p>
        <p class="py-4">Groups is our flagship app for communities of all shapes and sizes, needs and interests. You can build a space composed of channels with varying functionalities and permissions. Right now those functionalities include Talk for discussion, Notebook for writing, and Gallery for multimedia archiving. It’s like wrapping Discord, Medium and Tumblr into one clean and simple interface with a single login.</p>
        <p class="py-4">There are a lot of ways to use this. It could serve as a team communication tool connecting members of <a href="https://twitter.com/tloncorporation/status/1668684969483411456?s=20">various roles</a>. It could be a publishing platform for an individual looking to reach an audience in a more social way. Or it could be a place for updates between a group of friends.</p>
        <p class="py-4">Talk is our standalone communication app. In Talk—as well as its mobile counterpart Small Talk—you’ll find direct messages alongside all your Group discussions. It’s simple in its functionality, but shows off app interoperability really nicely. Only care about the chat functionality of Landscape? Just use Talk to cut through the rest and view all your conversations from across the network in one place.</p>
        <p class="py-4">Notebooks and Galleries are our next standalone apps, and we’ve got a few more up our sleeve after that.</p>
        
